description.narrative: In Gaza, 10,626 children (49% girls) accessed humanitarian child protection and psychosocial support through 12 family centres; over 2,073 children (1,368 boys and 705 girls) were met with urgent case management support, and 4,423 caregivers (76% women) were reached with awareness raising on positive parenting. In East Jerusalem, 2,800 vulnerable children at risk of detention were reached with prevention and protection services, and legal aid services provided to 410 child offenders, and 233 in Gaza. Two vocational centres diverted 20 children from detention, and 2,296 children were sensitised on their legal rights during arrest and detention. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
